entry.title: [wayland] Cancel dnd when drag target or dragged window destroyed
entry.content:
This CL updates the WaylandWindowDragController to cancel the dnd

session client-side when either of the drag target window or the

dragged window are destroyed.



The dnd session is not cancelled when either the pointer grab or

origin window are destroyed as this occurrence is already supported

and defined by the dnd code.



The client terminates the dnd session by calling OnDataSourceFinish()

which resets the wl_data_source and performs some client-side

cleanup. The spec indicates that the destruction of the data source

can be performed to cancel the dnd session.



To handle any possible events sent by the server, but not yet

received by the client after the dnd session has been cancelled, the

client will no-op any further dnd events after this has occurred.



Bug: b/278482149

entry.title: inputs: Introduce ExtendSelectionAndReplace/ReplaceSurroundingText API.
entry.content:
ChromeOS has a common operation of "replace some existing text around

the cursor with some new text". This is used in autocorrection, grammar

check, longpress diacritics etc.



This is currently accomplished by doing ExtendSelectionAndDelete (aka

DeleteSurroundingText), followed by a InsertText (aka CommitText).

There are two problems with this:



1) Because it's not atomic, users may see a brief flash.



2) Some websites do not support ExtendSelectionAndDelete correctly.



Introduce a new ExtendSelectionAndReplace/ReplaceSurroundingText API

that can be used by longpress diacritics on ChromeOS. Blink already

supports this operation for Mac, and we can fallback to the two

separate operations for other clients.



Bug: b/279670207,1443726

entry.title: [scheduler] IdleHelper stores a raw pointer to TaskQueue
entry.content:
(3/8) of TaskQueue lifetime refactor, which will make sequence manager

TaskQueue uniquely owned and a pure virtual interface implemented by

TaskQueueImpl.



IdleHelper has a scoped_refptr to a TaskQueue that will be uniquely

owned by the corresponding (Main|NonMain)ThreadTaskQueue. Since the

queue's lifetime matches that of IdleHelper, this converts the reference

to a raw pointer. Note we don't use a WeakPtr since the queue & helper

are created on the main thread for workers, so we'd need to change that

or update the weak ptr like we do for QueueEnabledVoters. Since we

should eventually use a common (ref-counted or garbage collected) base

class for blink task queues, we just store a raw pointer for now.

entry.title: [CrOS Cellular] Prevent cyclical shill calls to SetProperties().
entry.content:
Previously, we continuously sent revamp APNs to shill in ApnMigrator's

NetworkListChanged() when the flag is on, causing NetworkListChanged()

to be triggered recursively with each update to shill.



This CL adds a stopping condition where if the cellular network has

already been updated with the revamped APN list in shill, ApnMigrator

will no longer tell shill to update the network with the revamp

ApnList.



Note that each time the flag is flipped on, the set that keeps track

of the networks that APNs have already been sent to in shill will clear

because ApnMigrator will be constructed each time the flag is enabled

or disabled.



Fixed: b/280886640

Test: manual and unittest *ApnMigrator*

entry.title: [Extensions] Fix side panel icon not showing up for certain displays
entry.content:
The reason why this happens is because different display request

different scale factors for the extension's icon (i.e. 27 inch external

monitor requests 1x, and a Macbook pro 16 inch screen requests 2x).



If the representation for a requested scale factor is not found at

paint time, then it is requested when an action (i.e. mouseover, or

or repainting) is taken.



The solution involves loading all supported scale factors upfront.

Also, since the extension's side panel icon will always point to the

same image skia, the `OnExtensionIconImageChanged` call was not

necessary (doesn't seem to affect tests either).

entry.title: Use base::i18n::GetConfiguredLocale() for the CountryNames singleton.
entry.content:
The motivation is to get rid of the `CountryNames::SetLocaleString()`,

which caused (not being called in time) some issues in the past.



Why this should work:

`l10n_util::GetApplicationLocale(string)` is used [1] at the initial

stages of different environments loading, this getter also set

the ICU default locale (base::i18n::SetICUDefaultLocale), which is

being returned by `base::i18n::GetConfiguredLocale()`.

e.g. `g_browser_process->GetApplicationLocale()` returns the locale

determined during `ui::ResourceBundle::LoadLocaleResources` [2].

`l10n_utils` is eventually used in CountryNamesForLocale [3]

entry.title: Revert "Clear the main page selection when the side panel selection clears."
entry.content:
This reverts commit 0c6cb33a628e090624ee3170f51545fb5171c524.



Reason for revert: This CL causes the main page to jump to the top

when the user makes a null selection, losing the user's scroll

position. The goal of selecting is to let a user be able to easily

keep the main page and reading pane in sync, but when the scroll

jumps, it's jarring and the user loses their place.



Screen recordings:

With the original CL (notice jumping): https://drive.google.com/file/d/1n7DEIOMbSqMyG1aHc2nJRpf5-gGO_632/view?usp=sharing

With the CL reverted (notice no more jumping):

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1UklMhBGutD14ZoWr0FEJDglBlxFUUIjx/view?usp=sharing



The bug that the original CL was fixing is not as severe as the bug

it introduced, which is why I propose a revert.



Original change's description:

> Clear the main page selection when the side panel selection clears.

>

> Previously, the main page would keep the highlight even if the side panel clears.

>

> One quirk: clicking inside the existing selection on the side panel returns a null anchor and focus node, while clicking outside the existing selection does not. Both actions clear the side panel's selection but I had to add a check for those null nodes and force clear the selection.

>

> Demo: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KcDsEvOmw7JXR25VpsMUAaBQYVuC_Pwm/view?usp=sharing&resourcekey=0-E73EqINVqjbB2HzZtqS7zA

navigation to a potentially matching URL happens before the browser

receives the headers, but after the browser makes the prefetch request.



In order to synchronize the navigation we are introducing a new

python handler which will synchronize the in flight prefetch with the

WPT test by using request.server.stash.



Flow:

* prefetch

prefetch_nvs_hint.py?uuid=...&nvs_header=...&otherqueryparams

* the prefetch request above includes no_vary_search_hint in

speculation rules

* the server blocks progress on this prefetch request on the server

side so from the browser perspective the server is "thinking"

* the test starts navigation to

prefetch_nvs_hint.py?uuid=...&nvs_header=...&otherqueryparams.

This navigation matches by No-Vary-Search hint the above in

progress prefetch.

* the test fetches prefetch_nvs_hint.py?uuid=...&unblock="unblock"

which unblocks the in progress prefetch so that the in-progress

navigation can continue

entry.title: Make StringToNumber() skip leading whitespace using ASCII, not C locale.
entry.content:
For narrow strings, this shouldn't be a behavior change, but for wider

strings, iswspace() would have returned true on a variety of Unicode

whitespace that will no longer be skipped.



If we truly wanted to support Unicode whitespace, we should have done it

using the ICU functions to iterate codepoints, so that we could have

properly detected it in UTF-8 strings; and we also should have used ICU

to detect the whitespace, so it would not vary based on the C locale,

which is never the right determinant of localized behavior in Chrome.



APIs that called to here, like StringToInt(), are vaguely documented;

they don't say what encoding they expect. I doubt anyone was actually

relying on Unicode whitespace being skipped. Enforce that.
